ibution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the very numerous places called Clifton, from Old English <i>clif</i> ‘slope’ (see   Cliff  ) + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’."],"variants":[{"name":"Cliff","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of numerous places called Cliff(e), Cle(e)ve, or Clive, from Old English <i>clif</i> ‘slope, bank, cliff’, or a topographic name from the same word. The Old English word was used not only in the sense of modern English <i>cliff</i> but also of much gentler slopes and frequently also of a riverbank or seashore."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Robert Clifton was born in 1291, in Clifton, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Gervase Clifton, was 19 and his mother, Alice Rabacy, was 16. He married Emma Moton about 1308, in Clifton, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died before 1327."},"et":{"1291–Bef 1327":"1291–enne 1327","1291–1327":"1291–1327","1293–1354":"1293–1354","1293–Female":"1293–Surnud","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1318–1378":"1318–1378","1272–1316":"1272–1316","1276–1299":"1276–1299","Aft 1299":"pärast 1299","1272":"1272","Abt 1308":"umbes 1308","1293":"1293","1291":"1291","Bef 1327":"enne 1327","1316":"1316","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1378":"1378","1299":"1299","1354":"1354","1276":"1276","1318":"1318","Clifton, Nottingham district, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Clifton, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Clifton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Clifton, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Clifton-with-Glapton, Nottingham district, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Clifton, Nottingham, England":"Clifton, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Clifton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Clifton, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1291–Bef 1327":"1291–ennen vuotta 1327","1291–1327":"1291–1327","1293–1354":"1293–1354","1293–Female":"1293–Kuollut","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","1318–1378":"1318–1378","1272–1316":"1272–1316","1276–1299":"1276–1299","Aft 1299":"1299 jälkeen","1272":"1272","Abt 1308":"noin 1308","1293":"1293","1291":"1291","Bef 1327":"ennen vuotta 1327","1316":"1316","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1378":"1378","1299":"1299","1354":"1354","1276":"1276","1318":"1318","Clifton, Nottingham district, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Clifton, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Clifton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Clifton, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Clifton-with-Glapton, Nottingham district, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Clifton, Nottingham, England":"Clifton, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Clifton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Clifton, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fr":{"1291